1
00:00:43,043 --> 00:00:44,378
Do you want to go get tteokbokki?

2
00:00:44,462 --> 00:00:45,379
Okay.

3
00:00:45,463 --> 00:00:47,089
CHAPTER 12: YOU GUYS WANT TO GO OUT
INTO THE REAL WORLD, RIGHT?

4
00:00:55,097 --> 00:00:56,766
Oh, hello, sir.

5
00:00:56,849 --> 00:00:59,268
-Eui-ju! Are you still here?
-Yes.

6
00:00:59,351 --> 00:01:01,729
I'm going to drop by the library.

7
00:01:03,147 --> 00:01:04,315
Is something bothering you?

8
00:01:07,943 --> 00:01:09,361
I think

9
00:01:09,445 --> 00:01:11,822
my homeroom teacher has it in for me.

10
00:01:13,157 --> 00:01:14,325
Why?

11
00:01:15,159 --> 00:01:18,078
Ever since that misunderstanding
about the filming,

12
00:01:18,162 --> 00:01:20,039
he's been acting like he hates me.

13
00:01:21,624 --> 00:01:22,500
No way.

14
00:01:23,459 --> 00:01:24,668
It's true.

15
00:01:24,752 --> 00:01:28,130
First, he embarrassed me in front
of everyone by asking me my math score.

16
00:01:28,214 --> 00:01:31,300
Then he made me write an apology
because I said I hated math.

17
00:01:31,383 --> 00:01:34,011
And now he's giving me demerits
for a ridiculous reason.

18
00:01:35,554 --> 00:01:37,723
He wouldn't do that for no reason.

19
00:01:44,063 --> 00:01:45,064
Goodbye.

20
00:01:45,773 --> 00:01:47,983
See you tomorrow.

21
00:01:53,948 --> 00:01:55,199
Hey, Yoon!

22
00:01:55,282 --> 00:01:57,451
I thought you wanted
to take Discrete Math together.

23
00:01:58,911 --> 00:02:00,496
No, no, no.

24
00:02:03,833 --> 00:02:06,085
This ending is lame.

25
00:02:06,168 --> 00:02:10,130
Tae-ha can't let Si-on just walk away.

26
00:02:10,214 --> 00:02:11,173
The math…

27
00:02:12,132 --> 00:02:12,967
I mean,

28
00:02:13,676 --> 00:02:14,552
Ju Si-on.

29
00:02:15,302 --> 00:02:17,096
You deserve a beating.

30
00:02:18,389 --> 00:02:19,598
It's going to hurt.

31
00:02:19,682 --> 00:02:22,560
Blame it on the personality
of the person you're based on.

32
00:02:26,772 --> 00:02:27,690
Good.

33
00:02:29,859 --> 00:02:31,443
HIS EYES BLAZE WITH OBSESSION…

34
00:02:33,779 --> 00:02:34,655
Hey, Ju Si-on!

35
00:02:39,952 --> 00:02:41,120
TAE-HA PUNCHES SI-ON

36
00:02:50,713 --> 00:02:52,298
-Let's go.
-You're bleeding.

37
00:02:52,381 --> 00:02:53,799
-I'm fine.
-Hang on a second.

38
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,552
One punch just isn't enough. Do it again.

39
00:02:56,635 --> 00:02:58,012
Sorry?

40
00:03:00,306 --> 00:03:01,181
-Again?
-One more?

41
00:03:02,474 --> 00:03:03,934
Just a moment!

42
00:03:12,026 --> 00:03:12,985
There we go.

43
00:03:13,068 --> 00:03:14,737
That hits the spot.

44
00:03:16,405 --> 00:03:17,323
That's better!

45
00:03:23,078 --> 00:03:24,121
This is really great.

46
00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:27,583
How can I keep it to myself?

47
00:03:31,086 --> 00:03:32,296
Shall I just upload it?

48
00:03:36,175 --> 00:03:37,009
Right?

49
00:03:37,968 --> 00:03:41,013
You guys want to go out
into the real world, right?

50
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:44,725
If I'm this excited,

51
00:03:44,808 --> 00:03:47,561
you guys must be even more so.

52
00:03:48,687 --> 00:03:51,774
-Do it!
-Do it!

53
00:03:51,857 --> 00:03:54,151
-Do it!
-Do it!

54
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:56,028
-Do it!
-Do it!

55
00:03:56,111 --> 00:03:57,529
Shall I just upload it?

56
00:04:11,293 --> 00:04:12,878
Nobody's going to find out.

57
00:04:23,472 --> 00:04:24,598
SUBMIT A NEW PROJECT

58
00:04:29,770 --> 00:04:32,773
-We're going out into the real world!
-We're going out into the real world!

59
00:04:32,856 --> 00:04:34,316
WE WERE FRIENDS

60
00:04:41,907 --> 00:04:45,619
CHAPTER 13: ARE HIS GLASSES
REALLY THAT BIG A DEAL?

61
00:04:51,458 --> 00:04:53,627
EPISODE 4

62
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:56,130
Is it that bad?

63
00:04:59,717 --> 00:05:00,634
I'll be okay.

64
00:05:01,218 --> 00:05:03,470
Why would someone take glasses
they can't even use?

65
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:06,390
That's it!

66
00:05:08,392 --> 00:05:09,476
Up in a tree.

67
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:11,061
You said you threw them.

68
00:05:11,145 --> 00:05:13,188
If they're not on the ground,
they must be in a tree.

69
00:05:14,189 --> 00:05:16,108
I thought of that,
so I looked on the way home.

70
00:05:16,191 --> 00:05:17,026
They weren't there.

71
00:05:18,694 --> 00:05:19,945
So where have they gotten to?

72
00:05:20,863 --> 00:05:22,865
Did a pigeon take them to build its nest?

73
00:05:24,074 --> 00:05:25,159
Yes!

74
00:05:25,242 --> 00:05:27,911
They do say that magpies and such
like shiny things.

75
00:05:27,995 --> 00:05:30,956
Apparently, sometimes they take them
to decorate their nests.

76
00:05:32,916 --> 00:05:34,251
Just get some new ones.

77
00:05:34,334 --> 00:05:37,755
The problem is it's not that
straightforward to make new ones.

78
00:05:40,132 --> 00:05:41,300
Are you done?

79
00:05:42,551 --> 00:05:43,677
He's hardly eaten anything.

80
00:05:45,304 --> 00:05:46,388
They're in a nest.

81
00:06:19,046 --> 00:06:19,963
What's wrong with him?

82
00:06:23,717 --> 00:06:24,843
I think he's really sick.

83
00:06:28,931 --> 00:06:30,516
I think I need to take a sick day.

84
00:06:31,141 --> 00:06:33,310
Okay, I'll let them know at school.

85
00:06:34,103 --> 00:06:35,145
Get some rest.

86
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:38,816
Laid low by a pair of glasses.

87
00:06:59,962 --> 00:07:01,630
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

88
00:07:17,229 --> 00:07:19,398
Mr. Ga is feeling unwell,

89
00:07:19,481 --> 00:07:21,859
so I'll be taking homeroom today.

90
00:07:21,942 --> 00:07:23,277
Let's start with roll call.

91
00:07:24,027 --> 00:07:25,362
-Kim Ga-yeong.
-Here!

92
00:07:26,530 --> 00:07:27,489
Kim Dan-ji.

93
00:07:28,365 --> 00:07:30,242
-Here!
-Kim Yeong-jae.

94
00:07:30,325 --> 00:07:31,410
Here.

95
00:07:31,493 --> 00:07:33,078
-Oh A-rin.
-Here.

96
00:07:33,162 --> 00:07:34,371
I hope our teacher changes.

97
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:36,790
-Choi Yu-mi.
-It'd be amazing if it was Dong-ju.

98
00:07:36,874 --> 00:07:38,500
-Right?
-Yeah.

99
00:07:39,168 --> 00:07:40,586
-Jeon Ji-min.
-Here.

100
00:07:42,921 --> 00:07:45,799
He looked fine yesterday.

101
00:07:46,550 --> 00:07:48,760
Maybe he bunked off
to hang out with his girlfriend.

102
00:07:48,844 --> 00:07:51,346
That would be amazing.

103
00:07:51,430 --> 00:07:54,975
He's being punished
for being mean to Eui-ju.

104
00:07:55,058 --> 00:07:57,227
Giving my girl demerits for no reason.

105
00:07:57,311 --> 00:07:58,854
-Right?
-Yeah.

106
00:08:00,355 --> 00:08:01,231
Cute.

107
00:08:03,609 --> 00:08:05,736
-Jenny, do you ever diet?
-Why?

108
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:10,824
Hello, Mr. Ga. Are you okay?

109
00:08:13,035 --> 00:08:15,746
Oh, no! Please take good care of yourself.

110
00:08:16,580 --> 00:08:18,373
Don't worry about us.

111
00:08:19,875 --> 00:08:22,586
I'll make sure to tell the others
in homeroom.

112
00:08:23,921 --> 00:08:26,340
Okay. Get some rest.

113
00:08:42,564 --> 00:08:45,025
I explained
the concept of Rolle's Theorem.

114
00:08:45,108 --> 00:08:48,487
If we insert one here…

115
00:08:50,364 --> 00:08:53,075
And if we insert five here…

116
00:08:56,578 --> 00:08:57,621
Great work.

117
00:08:57,704 --> 00:08:59,873
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

118
00:08:59,957 --> 00:09:01,291
We're done.

119
00:09:01,375 --> 00:09:02,251
I'm so sleepy.

120
00:09:02,876 --> 00:09:04,878
I'm so sleepy.

121
00:09:05,587 --> 00:09:07,089
Guys, can I have your attention?

122
00:09:07,172 --> 00:09:09,341
Is Mr. Ga not coming to school
tomorrow either?

123
00:09:11,051 --> 00:09:14,513
Applications for after-school programs
are due by tomorrow so don't forget.

124
00:09:15,472 --> 00:09:16,306
That's all.

125
00:09:18,558 --> 00:09:21,645
-Did she just ignore me?
-Yeah.

126
00:09:21,728 --> 00:09:22,938
I'm off to art academy.

127
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:24,564
Bye.

128
00:09:29,486 --> 00:09:31,321
Is he really sick?

129
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:34,825
It's none of my business.

130
00:09:39,997 --> 00:09:42,874
MISSING GLASSES

131
00:09:42,958 --> 00:09:45,085
At this rate, he'll have
to take a leave of absence.

132
00:09:47,045 --> 00:09:48,088
What did the doctor say?

133
00:09:48,171 --> 00:09:50,048
He has to keep resting.

134
00:09:50,132 --> 00:09:52,175
If he overdoes it,
he risks damaging his other eye.

135
00:09:53,218 --> 00:09:54,594
Oh, hello.

136
00:09:55,178 --> 00:09:56,471
Is that your application form?

137
00:09:57,597 --> 00:10:00,309
What's up with Mr. Ga's glasses?

138
00:10:01,977 --> 00:10:02,894
The thing is…

139
00:10:05,230 --> 00:10:06,523
MISSING GLASSES

140
00:10:07,316 --> 00:10:10,485
Are his glasses really that big a deal?

141
00:10:14,364 --> 00:10:16,199
They're special glasses.

142
00:10:17,409 --> 00:10:19,411
He was trying to soldier on,
but in the end…

143
00:10:20,746 --> 00:10:22,831
It's going to take a long time
to make new ones.

144
00:10:22,914 --> 00:10:24,041
I'm quite worried.

145
00:10:34,926 --> 00:10:36,803
Oh! No!

146
00:10:41,516 --> 00:10:43,101
Hey!

147
00:10:43,185 --> 00:10:45,062
Ga-yun!

148
00:10:45,145 --> 00:10:47,356
-Stop!
-What is it?

149
00:10:47,439 --> 00:10:49,191
Let me borrow your bike for a bit.

150
00:10:49,274 --> 00:10:51,234
-My bike?
-I'll give it back later. Quickly!

151
00:10:51,318 --> 00:10:52,736
-Sure.
-Quick!

152
00:10:52,819 --> 00:10:53,779
Thank you.

153
00:10:59,868 --> 00:11:01,495
Move out the way.

154
00:11:01,578 --> 00:11:02,704
Hey!

155
00:11:17,761 --> 00:11:19,304
Hey!

156
00:11:20,055 --> 00:11:21,264
Hey!

157
00:11:22,724 --> 00:11:23,975
Come on!

158
00:11:32,442 --> 00:11:33,652
Wait!

159
00:11:33,735 --> 00:11:35,237
No!

160
00:11:36,363 --> 00:11:37,948
Come on!

161
00:11:38,031 --> 00:11:38,990
Wait!

162
00:11:43,578 --> 00:11:44,830
Stop!

163
00:11:44,913 --> 00:11:46,373
Hey! Please!

164
00:11:51,545 --> 00:11:53,088
Hey!

165
00:11:57,008 --> 00:11:58,051
Hey!

166
00:12:07,477 --> 00:12:08,478
Hey!

167
00:12:12,149 --> 00:12:13,775
Please!

168
00:12:13,859 --> 00:12:16,528
How far are you going?

169
00:12:18,405 --> 00:12:20,198
Please stop!

170
00:12:23,410 --> 00:12:24,995
Mister!

171
00:12:35,714 --> 00:12:38,341
What the hell are you doing?
It's dangerous!

172
00:12:38,425 --> 00:12:39,718
I'm sorry.

173
00:12:39,801 --> 00:12:41,052
But…

174
00:12:41,136 --> 00:12:43,054
You've got to help me.

175
00:12:43,138 --> 00:12:45,307
My teacher's going to die without them.

176
00:12:46,016 --> 00:12:47,601
What are you talking about?

177
00:12:48,351 --> 00:12:49,519
The thing is…

178
00:12:50,645 --> 00:12:54,065
I threw my teacher's glasses in the trash.

179
00:12:54,149 --> 00:12:56,485
But without them, he's going to die.

180
00:12:58,487 --> 00:13:00,280
Can you help me out?

181
00:13:00,363 --> 00:13:02,574
Please. They're in there.

182
00:13:04,326 --> 00:13:06,536
Please…

183
00:13:09,039 --> 00:13:11,917
MUNICIPAL DUMP

184
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,543
Are you sure they're in here?

185
00:13:13,627 --> 00:13:16,713
Yes, I threw them out yesterday.

186
00:13:18,006 --> 00:13:19,883
Why would you do that?

187
00:13:20,550 --> 00:13:22,052
I know.

188
00:13:23,094 --> 00:13:24,471
And why look for them again?

189
00:13:25,347 --> 00:13:26,640
I know.

190
00:13:27,933 --> 00:13:29,476
I'm really sorry.

191
00:13:29,559 --> 00:13:30,685
I'll be as quick as I can.

192
00:13:37,609 --> 00:13:38,777
Mister.

193
00:13:38,860 --> 00:13:40,403
I'm really grateful.

194
00:13:40,487 --> 00:13:41,404
I'll search.

195
00:13:41,488 --> 00:13:43,740
I'll be really quick
and clear it all up again.

196
00:13:58,964 --> 00:14:00,090
Oh, look.

197
00:14:00,173 --> 00:14:01,466
I've found them.

198
00:14:01,550 --> 00:14:02,551
Is that them?

199
00:14:03,552 --> 00:14:04,844
These are the ones.

200
00:14:11,351 --> 00:14:13,311
Thank you.

201
00:14:13,395 --> 00:14:14,437
Thank you so much.

202
00:14:14,521 --> 00:14:18,567
CHAPTER 14: YOU BREAKING MY GLASSES CAUSED
TEN MILLION WON'S WORTH OF DAMAGE

203
00:14:24,489 --> 00:14:25,448
Where did you find them?

204
00:14:27,450 --> 00:14:29,160
They were on the bench with poop on it.

205
00:14:29,244 --> 00:14:30,662
They were already broken.

206
00:14:35,959 --> 00:14:37,002
4073.

207
00:14:41,214 --> 00:14:43,091
That's the last four digits
of your phone number.

208
00:14:46,011 --> 00:14:49,264
One of my students has the same number.

209
00:14:54,311 --> 00:14:56,104
YEO EUI-JU

210
00:14:56,646 --> 00:14:57,564
What's your name?

211
00:15:00,108 --> 00:15:01,651
Why is that important?

212
00:15:01,735 --> 00:15:04,237
Just give me the money.
I have to go to PC room.

213
00:15:04,779 --> 00:15:05,655
Name.

214
00:15:06,239 --> 00:15:07,407
Yeo Eui-do.

215
00:15:11,620 --> 00:15:12,621
Call your sister.

216
00:15:13,371 --> 00:15:14,372
Why?

217
00:15:15,206 --> 00:15:16,041
Just do it.

218
00:15:28,803 --> 00:15:31,056
Hi, what is it?

219
00:15:31,139 --> 00:15:32,849
There's someone who wants to talk to you.

220
00:15:38,313 --> 00:15:39,189
Yeo Eui-ju.

221
00:15:48,865 --> 00:15:50,659
You stole your teacher's glasses?

222
00:15:50,742 --> 00:15:51,785
You're nuts.

223
00:15:53,578 --> 00:15:54,996
Now she's here, you can go.

224
00:15:56,247 --> 00:15:57,582
And talk to her nicely.

225
00:16:08,677 --> 00:16:09,636
Sir.

226
00:16:11,054 --> 00:16:13,723
So what happened was…

227
00:16:13,807 --> 00:16:17,018
I clearly asked
if you'd stepped on my glasses.

228
00:16:18,478 --> 00:16:21,856
You could have said something when we were
all looking, or again in the parking lot.

229
00:16:24,651 --> 00:16:27,362
But you looked me right in the eye
and said it wasn't you.

230
00:16:28,780 --> 00:16:29,656
I…

231
00:16:30,657 --> 00:16:31,574
I was scared…

232
00:16:32,701 --> 00:16:35,870
I'd get in trouble for breaking them.

233
00:16:37,372 --> 00:16:38,998
But…

234
00:16:39,082 --> 00:16:41,626
You gave me four demerits because of Ji-a.

235
00:16:41,710 --> 00:16:44,003
I don't think I did anything wrong.

236
00:16:44,671 --> 00:16:46,464
It seemed so unfair.

237
00:16:47,048 --> 00:16:50,009
And I feel like you hate me.

238
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:54,723
I was wrong.

239
00:16:56,766 --> 00:16:59,519
I didn't know they were special glasses.

240
00:16:59,602 --> 00:17:01,563
If I knew your eyes were so bad,

241
00:17:01,646 --> 00:17:03,648
I'd have given them back to you
straightaway.

242
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:07,068
I shouldn't have done what I did.

243
00:17:07,861 --> 00:17:09,821
I'm truly sorry.

244
00:17:34,721 --> 00:17:35,597
So.

245
00:17:36,723 --> 00:17:38,850
It was clearly your fault
and you've admitted it.

246
00:17:39,476 --> 00:17:40,935
All that's left is compensation.

247
00:17:41,728 --> 00:17:42,729
Compensation?

248
00:17:44,022 --> 00:17:46,941
You breaking my glasses caused
ten million won's worth of damage.

249
00:17:47,650 --> 00:17:49,152
Ten million won?

250
00:17:49,235 --> 00:17:51,070
What kind of glasses cost ten million won?

251
00:17:52,155 --> 00:17:54,157
I can't take money from a student.

252
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:56,326
So you'll have to find another way
to repay me.

253
00:17:57,368 --> 00:17:58,203
Okay.

254
00:17:58,828 --> 00:18:00,330
I will.

255
00:18:00,413 --> 00:18:02,582
However I can. Whatever it takes.

256
00:18:03,374 --> 00:18:04,834
I'll give you one chance.

257
00:18:07,045 --> 00:18:08,463
Thank you, sir.

258
00:18:08,546 --> 00:18:10,006
I'll do anything.

259
00:18:10,882 --> 00:18:11,841
After-school math.

260
00:18:13,426 --> 00:18:14,302
Sorry?

261
00:18:14,385 --> 00:18:16,054
I'm going to give you the chance

262
00:18:16,137 --> 00:18:18,640
to rediscover your passion for math
and improve your grades.

263
00:18:20,517 --> 00:18:21,935
What's the point?

264
00:18:23,228 --> 00:18:26,439
Sir, that class is only for smart kids.

265
00:18:26,523 --> 00:18:27,899
The ones who are top of the class.

266
00:18:28,650 --> 00:18:31,820
Before class,
set the temperature to 23 degrees,

267
00:18:31,903 --> 00:18:34,447
put the handouts on the desks,

268
00:18:34,531 --> 00:18:35,657
and collect any homework.

269
00:18:35,740 --> 00:18:38,952
After class, clean up,
put everything away, and lock the door.

270
00:18:39,577 --> 00:18:40,787
I really can't.

271
00:18:44,624 --> 00:18:45,667
Wednesday at five.

272
00:18:46,459 --> 00:18:47,627
Wednesday at five?

273
00:18:48,753 --> 00:18:51,965
Sir, I'm supposed to do after-school PE
at that time.

274
00:18:52,048 --> 00:18:54,092
I really can't do Wednesday at five.

275
00:18:58,471 --> 00:18:59,472
Don't forget.

276
00:19:02,141 --> 00:19:03,268
Ten million won.

277
00:19:14,195 --> 00:19:16,072
I really can't.

278
00:19:18,116 --> 00:19:19,492
What am I going to do?

279
00:19:35,216 --> 00:19:37,176
What?

280
00:19:37,260 --> 00:19:38,177
My reward.

281
00:19:38,803 --> 00:19:40,138
I didn't get it because of you.

282
00:19:40,221 --> 00:19:41,556
Hey!

283
00:19:41,639 --> 00:19:44,809
What money do I have?
I already spent my allowance.

284
00:19:46,728 --> 00:19:48,229
-Mom!
-Wait!

285
00:19:49,188 --> 00:19:50,231
Okay.

286
00:19:56,571 --> 00:19:58,031
This is all I have.

287
00:19:59,532 --> 00:20:00,992
You should learn to budget.

288
00:20:10,126 --> 00:20:12,837
Why of all people did it have to be him
to get dirt on me?

289
00:20:12,921 --> 00:20:14,005
So annoying!

290
00:20:14,797 --> 00:20:16,591
So annoying!

291
00:20:21,429 --> 00:20:22,263
Hang on.

292
00:20:22,347 --> 00:20:24,432
It's clearly your fault
and you've admitted it.

293
00:20:25,058 --> 00:20:26,476
All that's left is compensation.

294
00:20:26,935 --> 00:20:28,895
Don't forget. Ten million won.

295
00:20:29,604 --> 00:20:32,523
He does come up with
a lot of really great dialogue.

296
00:20:43,201 --> 00:20:45,328
I bet mine's been buried way down again.

297
00:20:54,629 --> 00:20:55,672
WEB NOVEL RANKING

298
00:20:55,755 --> 00:20:56,923
Number one?

299
00:20:59,050 --> 00:21:00,259
Hang on a second.

300
00:21:00,343 --> 00:21:03,096
1. WE WERE FRIENDS
VIEWS: 130K

301
00:21:05,848 --> 00:21:07,600
WE WERE FRIENDS

302
00:21:07,684 --> 00:21:08,768
What the heck?

303
00:21:10,061 --> 00:21:11,145
How many favorites?

304
00:21:12,313 --> 00:21:13,982
One, ten,

305
00:21:14,732 --> 00:21:16,401
hundred…

306
00:21:16,484 --> 00:21:17,527
FAVORITES 15,320

307
00:21:17,610 --> 00:21:19,445
15,320?

308
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:22,156
What's going on?

309
00:21:23,241 --> 00:21:25,076
Is this definitely mine?

310
00:21:27,954 --> 00:21:29,038
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 1

311
00:21:33,167 --> 00:21:36,421
I'm from the future.
This novel is going to be huge.

312
00:21:36,504 --> 00:21:38,172
Please let Yoon and Si-on end up together.

313
00:21:38,256 --> 00:21:39,757
Tae-ha's in true love.

314
00:21:39,841 --> 00:21:41,384
Really looking forward to their story.

315
00:21:41,467 --> 00:21:42,301
What the heck?

316
00:21:45,847 --> 00:21:46,889
That hurt!

317
00:21:49,434 --> 00:21:50,351
Then…

318
00:21:51,060 --> 00:21:52,061
is this real?

319
00:21:52,145 --> 00:21:53,271
It's real?

320
00:21:57,900 --> 00:21:59,569
The tension is thick right from the off.

321
00:21:59,652 --> 00:22:02,405
-You could cut it with a knife.
-Tae-ha, you had me at red bean bread.

322
00:22:02,488 --> 00:22:04,282
Yoon is so much more complicated
than math.

323
00:22:04,365 --> 00:22:06,034
This line alone
tells the outlook of this story.

324
00:22:11,164 --> 00:22:12,832
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 2

325
00:22:16,753 --> 00:22:18,129
WHAT? AM I TOO CLOSE?
YOON SHOOK…

326
00:22:24,385 --> 00:22:25,970
Dan-ji found Mr. Noh's Instagram.

327
00:22:26,054 --> 00:22:28,097
I found photos of him
from back in college.

328
00:22:28,181 --> 00:22:29,182
Amazing!

329
00:22:29,265 --> 00:22:30,767
Can you try looking for Dong-ju's?

330
00:22:30,850 --> 00:22:32,643
How much are you going to pay me?

331
00:22:32,727 --> 00:22:33,936
Get lost.

332
00:22:34,020 --> 00:22:36,105
Why is Eui-ju so quiet?

333
00:22:36,189 --> 00:22:37,857
Is she actually studying?

334
00:22:39,192 --> 00:22:42,737
YOON SHOOK HIS HEAD BUT…

335
00:22:54,832 --> 00:22:55,666
You're late.

336
00:22:57,668 --> 00:22:58,753
I'm tired.

337
00:23:00,213 --> 00:23:01,047
We need to talk.

338
00:23:01,839 --> 00:23:02,840
I have nothing to say.

339
00:23:02,924 --> 00:23:05,051
If I say we talk, we talk, got it?

340
00:23:05,134 --> 00:23:06,677
-I said I have nothing…
-Shut up!

341
00:23:06,761 --> 00:23:07,595
Let go of me!

342
00:23:13,893 --> 00:23:14,769
Sorry.

343
00:23:15,269 --> 00:23:17,480
I told you to let go of me.

344
00:23:17,563 --> 00:23:18,898
Are you okay?

345
00:23:21,109 --> 00:23:23,277
It was clearly your fault
and you've admitted it.

346
00:23:25,029 --> 00:23:26,614
All that's left is compensation.

347
00:23:28,407 --> 00:23:29,367
Compensation?

348
00:23:34,622 --> 00:23:35,456
Ten million won.

349
00:23:37,333 --> 00:23:38,501
What?

350
00:23:38,584 --> 00:23:41,170
You splitting my lip caused
ten million won's worth of damage.

351
00:23:41,838 --> 00:23:43,506
What do you mean ten million won?

352
00:23:43,589 --> 00:23:45,508
Heard of a little thing
called "scarcity value"?

353
00:23:45,591 --> 00:23:47,718
The rarer something is,
the more valuable it becomes.

354
00:23:47,802 --> 00:23:49,762
Because people want it even more.

355
00:23:51,222 --> 00:23:53,641
Just like my lips,
which I don't just allow anyone to have.

356
00:23:56,853 --> 00:23:59,897
You're poor, so instead of money, you'll
have to find another way to repay me.

357
00:24:03,818 --> 00:24:05,069
Wednesday at five.

358
00:24:05,903 --> 00:24:06,863
Come to my place.

359
00:24:08,156 --> 00:24:09,740
Don't be even one second late.

360
00:24:15,454 --> 00:24:16,497
That ten million won.

361
00:24:21,627 --> 00:24:23,171
Pay me back properly.

362
00:24:48,446 --> 00:24:50,698
You're not treating her like that
on purpose, are you?

363
00:24:50,781 --> 00:24:52,825
Why are you being so strict with just her?

364
00:24:52,909 --> 00:24:55,995
Blink twice if you're here under duress.

365
00:24:56,078 --> 00:24:59,790
I can't accept her
only getting four points in math.

366
00:25:00,666 --> 00:25:02,376
You keep making me think bad thoughts.

367
00:25:02,460 --> 00:25:03,294
Yeo Eui-ju.

368
00:25:03,377 --> 00:25:05,254
I didn't realize
you were such a lost cause.

369
00:25:05,338 --> 00:25:06,297
I'm very disappointed.

370
00:25:06,380 --> 00:25:08,549
Is Tae-ha gonna be waiting
outside your house again?

371
00:25:08,633 --> 00:25:09,967
I don't know. Stop messing around.

372
00:25:10,843 --> 00:25:11,719
What's so funny?

373
00:25:11,802 --> 00:25:12,678
Is it R-rated?

374
00:25:13,179 --> 00:25:14,722
It's not like BL, is it?

375
00:25:14,805 --> 00:25:17,433
Now that's a proper cliffhanger.

376
00:25:17,516 --> 00:25:20,019
There's no way
you can skip the next episode.

377
00:26:16,575 --> 00:26:18,577
Subtitle: Paul Carver

